title: "XYZ Decision Space Model: Policy-as-Code for Agentic AI Input Treatment"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Haider
    given-names: Luke
version: "0.4-draft"
date-released: "2026-05-14"
abstract: >
  The XYZ Decision Space Model is a policy-as-code framework for governing
  semantic input treatment in agentic AI pipelines. It assigns each data
  element a per-agent coordinate binding for treatment authority, validity
  stability, and consequence, producing posture envelopes that declare how
  agents may treat inputs before reasoning begins.
repository-code: "https://github.com/luke-haider/xyz-decision-space-model"
